Kilicdaroglu Pledges to Close University Watchdog, Milliyet Says

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-03-21T06:30:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/kilicdaroglu-pledges-to-close-university-watchdog-milliyet-says.html
The leader of  Turkey ’s main
opposition party pledged to abolish the Higher Education
Council, which regulates universities, Milliyet newspaper
reported.  Republican People’s Party leader  Kemal Kilicdaroglu  told an
election rally in Eregli, northern Turkey, that his party would
close the council, stop charges at universities, and give
colleges greater autonomy, the newspaper said.    Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
